structures and theoretically predict\nthat such a symmetry breaking can lead to a giant MCA effect. Our prediction is\nconfirmed via experiments on thin bulk-insulating\n(Bi$_{1-x}$Sb$_{x}$)$_2$Te$_3$ TI nanowires, in which we observe an MCA\nconsistent with theory and $|\\gamma| \\sim 100000$ ${\\rm A^{-1} T^{-1}}$, the\nlargest ever reported MCA rectification coefficient in a normal conductor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 11 Sep 2021 04:59:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 12 May 2022 16:02:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-13"}
